The Math & Pipeline Strategy for this Specific Chart
Because this chart relies entirely on Quarterly data, its isolated pipeline will look slightly different than the other monthly charts.

Slice & Drop: Pull just these two columns and run your .dropna() step. This will leave you with a clean, unpadded grid containing data points exactly once every 3 months.

Do Not Forward-Fill Here: While we used .ffill() in the master engine to help line up quarterly data next to monthly data, you should not use forward-fill for this specific chart. If you forward-fill these metrics, a bar chart of QoQ growth will show three identical bars for every single quarter, which distorts the actual economic reality.

Keep the Quarterly Index: Keep this chart's DataFrame indexed strictly to the actual quarterly reporting months (e.g., March, June, September, December). When you pass this clean, 3-month interval DataFrame straight to your charting library, it will render perfect, crisp bars and lines without any artificial duplicate steps.

